ed life. Citizens who are "free spirits" deliver great benefits to liberal democracies, primarily by combatting dogmatism and fanaticism and the putative authority of public opinion.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aLiberalism. 0aPolitical sciencexPhilosophy. 4aCultural Studies : Identity. 4aHistory : Intellectual History. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Philosophy. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Theory. 4aPolitics and Law : Politics. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / History & Theory.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2020z978311149149340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143847979840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438479798423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438479798/original  a978-3-11-149149-3  SUNY Press eBook Package 2020b2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles